metadata.name: Aquarelle #115
metadata.description:
Mimicking the art of watercolours.

Save as png:
Click “s”
or double click/tap

Resolution:
Default image width = 2000px and aspect ratio = 4:3.
Modify the image width between 2000px and 10000px by adding “&w=xxxx” to the url (e.g. &w=4000).
High resolutions are computationally expensive and may take a while.

Background:
The canvas background texture is visible by default. This can be toggled off by adding “&b=0” to the url.
The background scales with resolution to mimic a bigger canvas so it will look different at different resolutions.
At high resolutions a Moiré pattern may appear on the canvas background texture due to the way images are resized in the browser. It’s always recommended to download a full resolution version of the piece.

By KRANKARTA
Created on Firefox desktop 105.0 on 2022-11-11 in javascript and GLSL.
CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Patches #108
metadata.description:
This token generates a colorful abstract artwork that appears as watercolor on fabric. Project began as exploration of palettes used in famous masterpieces listed on Color Lisa web site. 97 color combinations used by great artists are applied here on abstract art.

Each piece is generated by bio inspired cellular automata in which colors from chosen palette are competing for domination on canvas. There are three different configurations of space fragmentation and each one is producing specific style.

metadata.name: Contort #200
metadata.description:
Contort is the result of combining several previously meaningless experiments and learnings into a single cohesive algorithm. The project comes in a variety of shapes, bends, twists, colors, and other variations.  

The artwork builds towards the end-result by rendering a fixed number of forms per frame to ensure a smooth rendering process. Rendering times can vary depending on which features are combined by the hash.

objkt.name: Urban Building: Where Are We Going? #114

metadata.name: Urban Building: Where Are We Going? #114
metadata.description:
This is a building generation made by pure code.

Urbanization at the almost everywhere in the world has stepped into an accelerating phase in last century. Buildings bring magnificent achievements and represent the human power over nature. But, following these tall and crowd buildings one by one, where are we going?

In this work, I generate different types of building with a special viewpoint, which represent different concepts of states we are going to. Hope you enjoy these varieties and coincidences.

Variables:
- 4 modes
- 4 environments
- 3 orbs
- 3 building density
- 3 building structures

Please be patient with drawing process.

metadata.name: Truchet Towers #210
metadata.description:
Curved Truchet tiling is laid down on a 3D plane forming an imaginary landscape of ripples.

The longest continuous line created by the tiling is removed, cutting a path through the terrain.
This occurs within 3D space and may or may not appear within the confines of the canvas frame,
but most likely will appear.

A tower rises up to wherever a circle is created by the tiling. Driven by the random
tiling, zero or several of these may appear within the frame. Shadows differ in each mint.

In addition to working on decorative tiling, Sébastien Truchet worked on canals and sundials,
forming the inspiration for the exploration of shade and shadow in this work.

Mints will have a variety of earth-tone background colors with each perspective of the scene
slightly different to produce diverse results.

As I researched Sébastien Truchet I learned that he worked with hydraulics and canal design,
as well as sundials. This became the inspiration for my new shading and shadowing technique used
in this piece.

For me this piece evokes a sense of agriculture, and connects me to an imaginary
landscape that could have looked familiar to Truchet in 18th century France.

This work was created with my own javascript, utilizing my polyline path helper library I
maintain at https://github.com/markroland/path-helper.

metadata.name: Unicorn #5787
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: glory hole$ #549
metadata.description:
our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

HUGE thank you to @PureSpider for the layered PNG template, this dream would not have been realized without you friend.
